values:
I'm at my Dad's work right now. Everyone in the office have gone off to a fancy Christmas doo (is that how you spell doo?) and I'm siiting here answering phone calls. It's quite fun telling every single person who calls 'No sorry they're out at the moment, can I take a message?' And I'm getting paid to do this which is even better. I'm quite hungry right now...
My other job at the restaurant is very cool. Mostly I'm just washing dishes all day but occasionally I get to peel garlic cloves or take the leaves off stalks of thyme. I even got to take a trip to Moore Wilsons on my first day of work. Twice! But that was only because I didn't get the right thing the first time - who knew that broad beans and green beans weren't the same thing? The chef's I work with are really nutty. My boss has nicknames for everyone like bubbles and poo.
Oh exciting news! I have a croquet set sitting in my room!! So who wants to play croquet? I'm thinking next Saturday at Churton Park Park and hopefully the weather will be beautifully sunny. Tea and scones afterwards is what I'm envisaging as well.
Agh, I so don't know what I'm doing with answering the phone! I just had a lady who wanted a fax redirected... I mean what? I just took down a bunch of numbers and hopefully someone else can understand my kryptic writing.
I'm also starting my christmas wrapping job on Monday. I'm looking forward to that. Hopefully I don't get any really picky people who think I can't wrap presents properly. Anyway probably should pay attention to answering the phone now.

I have not been on here in so long. What have I been doing?! Could it be that I found a life? No... I think I've just been stressing a bit about exams. I had French today. I did so badly in listening. I don't know what's wrong with me, when it comes to listening I just crap out. The writing was good though. I used the sentance "Il va de soi que" it takes subjunctive so it looks all year 13 structury.

I've had a very interesting time since I last went on here. Very interesting... lots of big problems have just snuck up on me then gone 'hello' right in front of my face. It has been quite frightening some of them. But that's what life is. A world full of surprises. I like to think of these surprises as nice learning oppertunities.

Ok I think thats enough rambelling about absolutely nothing. Back to study :( and listening to...

Relient K!

I have been extremely busy lately. My weekend was spent doing the chem & physics assignments and an english essay which was very very crap. Somehow I don't think I answered the qustion but waffled on about nothing. I also sewed Lina's stage challenge outfit for her. I feel very proud about this because I managed to sew it all by myself with no halp from my mum and it turned out how it was suppose to. Its a white see-through body suit and with the dodgy cutting out of the material the people had done it turned out really good. Although when my mum looked at it afterwards she said I had sewed the zip on wrong but it still worked fine so it didn't really bother me.

Isabella is so excited about being in the ski team this year, she's even more excited than me. She's roped Hester and Charis into being on the team as well and they're designing a hoody/zip up top (depends on cost) for us. They've already designed whats going on the back and its a picture of skier jumping, drawn by Natelle and since Natelle is awesome at drawing it looks very cool. They've also decided it's going to be blue, yes, its not the normal school colours but they said our school should branch out a bit some time. I don't think any of them realise that there can only be three skiers in the team... or that the competition is in the middle of mock exams... but I don't plan on bursting their bubble just yet. But Isabella's excitement has rubbed off on me and now I'm really looking forward to it.

My parents are going away to Brisbane for a week... without me! I've told my mum she has to buy lots of clothes. Hopefully she'll bring back something I like. I can't think of any more exciting news but I just have to say please comment on my entries. Because last time I had no comments and I felt very unloved :(

Noooooooooooo! We have to go back to school tomorrow. I don't wanna. I was just starting to get used to the holidays. Waking up at about ten in the morning and doing absolutely nothing all day. It's not fair *goes to cry in a corner*.

But moving onto nicer things I spent the last few days in Raumati which is right next to Paraparaumu with my mum and grandma, and I caught the train up there which was quite exciting. Just as I was about to leave home, to catch the bus into town to get the tain, my sister came home and said she would drive me to tawa, which is closer than town, so I could get the train from there. I refused her offer however and went and caught the bus anyway which I'm really glad I did because the train didn't stop anywhere in tawa so if I had gone with my sister's idea, I would have been standing on the platform in tawa watching the train go pass saying, "but..but.. I need to get that train."

In Paraparam we went to a bird wildlife place and I saw a tuatara and a kiwi. We also went to Lindale and I bought some fudge mmmmm.

This morning I went to church and one of the couples from our congregation told us a bit about their life. The husband used to design boats, get them built and then sell them for huge amounts of money. Needless to say they were quite rich. Then one day he went along to a free masonry meeting. Free Masonries are people who belong to a kind of club, which has been operating for ages, and they do lots of weird practises, it's a bit like a colt, and it's only for men. I'm not sure exactly what they do but apparently it's lots of freaky stuff.

Anyway this guy went to one of their meetings and it was an initiation meeting so I think he had to take some oaths. After the meeting he decided he never wanted to go back. After that one of his employees lost everything ie. his wife left him, someone in his family died and he went bankrupt. So the employee couldn't pay the guy what he owed, so the guy had to try to get loans off other people so he could carry on his business but no one would give him a loan. Eventually he started to go bankrupt too and his business fell through. He tried applying for other IT jobs (which he was trained in) but no one would employ him. In total he applied for 1200 jobs but no one would take him. His family had to sell most of their clothes, all their jewellery and ended up having an overdraft of $50,000 with the bank. They then applied for social welfare because they had absolutely no money to buy food with.

After living like this for a bit of time the wife came to the conclusion that their family was cursed. She looked up on the internet how to get rid of curses and she tried doing some rituals with candles and stuff, like witchcraft, but that didn't work. She then got hold of the pastor of our church and he went to their house and prayed in every room and over all their family.

During this whole time the little girl in their family had been having awfull nightmares and in the night she had heard voices which she thought were her parents, but they hadn't been talking. The night that our pastor prayed over them the little girl said she had a scary dream. The mother asked her why she hadn't called for her in the night like she usually did and the little girl said that she hadn't been frightened. The mother then said that she didn't have to be frightened anymore because they had been prayed over and the little girl said she knew that because all the monsters were gone.

A few days later the husband got a job offer from some company. And since then he kept on getting really good job offers.

It all started a couple of weeks ago as I was having a shower. A lovely little, brown weta decided he wanted to join me. He had a body that was about 7cm long and antenna thingys which were another 5cm long. I wasn't to keen on sharing my shower with another little creature so I promptly ran out of the shower and yelled at my mum to do something with my oversized little visitor. Then about a week ago the oversized little weta wanted to have a shower with me again, but this time he was already waiting for me in the shower. Again I wasn't very keen on sharing my shower so I yelled at my Dad to deal with the weta. I havn't seen my oversized little weta again but last night a delightful little spider decided he wanted to join me too in my shower. His body had a diameter of about 5cm. I think he had been talking to the weta because he was already in the shower waiting for me just as the weta had done. Again I ran out of the bathroom (with a towel around me of course for you dodgy people.. *cough* Karen *cough*) and yelled at my mum to deal with the extremely oversized visitor. He was promptly boiled and smoshed up while trying to get him down the plug hole. It's not that I don't like these oversized little visitors, for they are very beneficial for the environment, it's just that I don't like sharing my shower with other creatures and if you persist on wanting to share a shower with me you may end up being boiled and smoshed down the plug hole.

I passed the calc internal! I've never been so scared of failing something before in my life. Normally after I do a test and before I get my marks back, I know that I at least passed, and I'm only worried that I didn't get as high a mark as I would have liked. But with calc I wasn't sure if I would've passed, I was so scared I was going to fail. But it's all over now.. except for english. But at the moment my story is working out quite well, apart from the fact I think I have about 1000 words when I'm only suppose to have 800 and I still haven't finished, but that's alright. I get to do creative writing three times so it doesn't worry me that much.
ISCF on Friday is going to be really fun. I've decided we're going to have a big worship time. I'll be playing the guitar and singing, along with Bimba playing the piano and Marida (a sixth former) playing the drums. I can't wait. If any one would like to come, they are highly welcome. I think by the end of year I'm going to go broke though because of ISCF. I keep buying food from New World so people can eat while they're at the meeting but if I keep spending my money there will be none left... then woe is me.
I also got my bank statement yesterday and I calculated that I only need to get another $400 to pay back my dad for going to Germany and that will take only two months, so I will soon be free of debt. But then next year I will have one huge debt for uni but that's a long time away yet.
I have to have another rant about chemistry and Mr kfjghdk. I'll put it in a cut so you don't have to read about my bitterness

So, during physics Mr Sturman came up to me and said that he'd looked at my test, the one I got an A in, and that he thought I had undersood everything quite well and the only reason I got an A is because the test was set out differently to last year. That is absolute bull shit as it doesn't matter if a test is set out differently or not it still asks the same things. Plus I didn't answer any questions in the whole section about dry cells. Why? Because our teacher didn't teach us anything about it. Then after some mumbling Mr Sturman said, without actually saying, that I couldn't swap classes, why I don't know. Then I saw Ms Rhyburn during my free and complained so she said I should take action.. and write a letter to Ms McLeod stating the reasons why I think Mr kjdsfg is a crap teacher. I have started the letter but I'm not sure if I should really go through with it because I might get my teacher fired and do I really hate my teacher that much to go to all this trouble of writing a formal complaint. Please advise me people, I'm so confused and I have untill Friday to decide.
I also came up with my own little plan after I found I couldn't swap classes. That is to wag all my chemistry classes and get a note explaining my absence from my parents, which I'm sure they will agree to, and go into Mr Clarks class "informerly" which Mr Sturman did say I could do.

Yesterday was my birthday and although I didn't have a proper party or anything for my birthday it was still a very good day. I finished the famine at ten in the morning and then ate a bagel. That wasn't such a good day because I felt sick afterwards cause I hadn't eaten anything for 40 hours and my stomach had shrunk. The netball tournament was so much fun yesterday but now I am so sore, every time I walk my but hurts heaps it's not cool! But my team got 58 goals, with a little help from Jess and Lina's sneky scoring, but that means we raised $232. I also got to play for Kate's team who were sponsored by techtonics and I managed to look like I was really good at netball but that was because my partners were 4th formers. One very amusing moment during the day was while we trying to get people to donate money for world vision and there was this group of about four young guys who were wtching us play and we got about five of us to go up to them at different times to ask for donations and they wouldn't give any money to us until Lisa the German girl went up with her very short shorts and they donated $5 to her. We were all in hysterics at that.

Katie, Jess and Lina bought me Mini Mud Cake! and chocolate mmm and an eater egg for my birthday. There was so much chocolate but couldn't eat much of the chocolate because I was still feeling sick from my 40 hours non eating.

In the evening I went to a pot-luck dinner and my mum had baked me a birthday cake so all in all I had a good birthday. I also got a free world vision t-shirt from Isabella and it actually looks quite good on me.

Also I have an embarrasing moment.

Well, on Saturday I met up with my old youth group leader at Herbs cafe and was just talking to him about a whole lot of stuff that was happening in my life. But at one point he asked me a question that I really wanted to avoid so I lied and said everything was fine. But then he just kept asking me the same question in different words so I thought well I might as well tell him the truth. So I got as far as saying one sentance of the truth and then I broke down in tears. So there I was in the middle of a cafe crying. I wanted to crawl up in a little ball and die, I was so humiliated. I couldn't stop crying either the tears just kept coming and there was nothing I could do. Finally when I stopped crying after a few minutes my youth leader was able to talk to me but I was just so embarassed. It was a good thing that I realised I had a problem in that little area of my life because now it's all fixed but I just wish I hadn't had to realise while being humiliated.

Finally I have some time to actually sit down and do nothing, like go on the internet. Going on the internet takes a surprisingly long time to do because once I'm on I just keep going to more sites and then I look at the clock and about half an hour has gone by. I've never been able to work out where all that time went.

Ohh, Lydia showed me this really cool game you can put in your calculator where you "Find the magic number." It is so cool. I never knew that calculators could be so much fun. Now when I'm in maths and Ms Vanmilligin is ranting about maths that makes absolutely no sense I can play on my calculator. Just think of the hours of fun I'll have. :)

The chemistry internal was today. It was surprisingly very easy and I managed to get 14.1ml for all my titres, so I think I did pretty well. Also I finally understand chemistry! I have the really crap teacher who everyone hates and can't pronounce his name, so for the last week in chem I've been sitting there with a complete blank on my face. But on Wednesday I went to Lydia's chem class during my free period and it suddenly made so much sense. It just shows you how much of crap teacher Mr thingymebob is.

Here's the rest of Aimee's quiz, I finally had time to finish it.

Personal::
[gotten in a car accident]: No, I usually only try to get into cars with people who can drive well
[dyed your hair]: No. My hair is completely natural, although I'm getting a bit distressed becuase it's slowly turning brown and I want to stay blonde
[choked in front of people on my own spit or drink]: Yes, It's so embarrassing when I do
[gone to school in your pajamas]: No I usaully remember to get changed when I wake up
[gotten a detention]: Yes but not really a proper one because I did at lunch time instead of after school. There was once in Intermediate where I was talking too much and the teacher made me put a tick by my name on the board (meaning I would get a detention) but instead I just put an 'M' for my last name. hehehe
[loved someone so much that it made you cry]: Yes many times

::This or that::
[Cold/hot]: Cold
[Blue/red]: Blue
[Rain/snow]: Snow
[Give/receive]: Give probably, after someone gives me something I just forget about but when I give something I always have built up excitement about how they're going to react and the preparation of the present.
[Rose/daisy]: Rose
[Private school/public school]: Public
[Chocolate milk/plain milk:]: Plain
[Spring/fall]: I'm guessing Fall means Autumn, so I'll go with Fall, because that's when my birthday is! Only 10 more days to go! 
[History/science]: Science definately. I did History once in 3rd form and it was the worst choice of my life. Mind you it wasn't my choice, my dad made me do it
[Math/English]: Maths although calculus is really confusing at the moment with all the proofs but English is too wordy for me
[Country/rock]: Rock
[Cherry coke/vanilla coke]: I'm going with Vanilla coke cause I've never heard of cherry before
[Love/lust]: Love, it means so much more
[Sleep/eat]: That's a really hard choice, I love both quite alot... I'll go with eat because chocolate is so good mmmm chocolate

::Opposite::

[Do they know]: I'm pretty sure my friends know I like them, but the guy doesn't know, no. 
[What do you look for in the opposite sex]: Maybe funny, but that's not a neccessity, able to talk to and reasonably good looks
[Do you have a boyfriend/girlfriend]: No

::Do you like to::

[Give back rubs]: No, I hate massaging people cause it makes my hands feel all funny with the rubbing
[Take walks in the rain]: Only if I'm in my togs and already dripping wet
[Watch tv]: Yes! What kind of question is that? Yay for Scrubs and the OC
[Do homework]: No, I never do homework
[Talk on the phone]: Yes
[Go online]: Not really. I like to read everyones LJs but it takes so long and I could be doing other stuff
[Kiss]: It depends on with who
[Do freaky things]: Oh yes, but then people stare at me weirdly which is a bit uncomfortable


::Extras::
[What is your worst habit]: Lately it has been nibbling my nail, I don't bite it properly like Jen though. I really have to stop doing it cause it's going to gradually increase into a big habit which won't be good. I think it all started from having such a crap maths and chem teacher
[What song are you listening to right now]: Mikey Trousers by The Lads "And I will always be Mikey Trousers he is good enough for me..."
[What is your computer desk made out of]: Wood, what else would it be made out of?
[What was the last thing you ate]: Boysenberry ice-cream for desert
[What should you really be doing right now]: Probably my homework but as I said before I don't do homework so that's not going to happen. I could watch T.V 
[If you were a crayon, what color would you be]: Pale pink

::Now::
[Where are you]: In our Study
[Are you wearing any jewelry]: NO! This is shocking I must go put on some jewellery... ok now I'm wearing a ring
[When was the last time you showered]: Last night and I'll be having another one tonight
[What color pants do you have on right now]: Navy blue

All done. Mike you have to do the rest too.

I'm babysitting at the moment. I love babysitting cause all I do is watch TV, eat their food and go on their computer. But tonight the little boy who is about two and a half started crying so I had to try and comfort him. Which I did! I thought he might start crying even more when he saw me but no, he calmed down so now its all good.

Today I did nothing. The past few weekends I've been going out all the time so it felt quite strange to be doing nothing

I played croquet on Wednesday! It is so much fun. I can't believe I never played it before, I've missed out on so much humiliation and fun and singing. I even won my singles game. Wow! It had to be beginners luck

   I hope you don't mind but the quiz you did looked like much fun so I thought I'd do it too. Is that alright? If not I'll delete it

 

NUMBER..

[been kissed]: Yes

[been in love]: Yes

I don't know where the rest of the quiz went so that will have to be it and I'm sorry there are lots of big spaces I'm not enough of a computer geek to know how to get rid of them

I had to go to work for the last two days after school and it was really boring, nothing exciting ever happens. Except for two weeks ago when I arrived half an hour late and I thought my boss might fire me because she was really angry. I work at an old people's home and no I don't have to clean up old people's sick etc I just give out the supper and wash dishes. Some of the old people are really cute like one lady who I give supper to and half an hour later she's frogotten she had supper so she has another cup of tea. Another lady goes up and down in the lift constantly because she has nothing else to do but instead of pressing the down button she pushes the emergency button so it rings really loudly. It gets kind of annoying after a while but still is quite cute.

Lina's party on Sunday was so much fun. There were so many pretty shoes, beautiful dresses and tops and skirts. And there was so much good food! The musical chairs was also very amusing. It's weird that no matter how old I get I will always love playing party games. When it was just the C-Park girls left at Kitty's we watched Shrek 2. Puss in Boots is the most cutest cat ever! I love it so much. On Sunday morning I had to walk home and it was kind of embarrasing walking around Churton Park all dressed up.

Yesterday I had a meeting for ISCF. I'm so excited about leading it and all you guys have to come along and support me. I really don't care if you guys believe in God or not I just need support :) I've decided we're going to have lots of shared lunches and play heaps of games like Mafia!

Agghh Chris Bees is trying to find information about me! That really scares the crap out of me because he is so disgusting and gross *shudders* The only upside to the whole Chris Bees thing is that Mike said he would beat the crap out of Chris for me. I know it's not the nicest thing in the world but it's kind of sweet in a way.

Ok, I'm going to eat now

Yesterday I went to a concert yesterday with The Lads! and Paul Colman! Paul Colman used to be in a band called Paul Colman trio but then they split up which I was very devastated about so now it's just Paul Colman doing gigs by himself. He's still really good but I miss the trio :( Anyway last night I saw heaps of the people I had gone to Parachute with and it was like Parachute all over again and so I was very excited. (I'm still not over Parachute yet). The only sad thing about the concert was that every one there was sitting down in the rows of chairs and weren't very enthusiastic at all so us Parachute people went up the front and started making a mosh pit of our own. There was only about 15 of us but it was still really fun. I also got free cake! Thankyou .

Yay! Lina's birthday is on Saturday and I have a really cool present for her. So many sequins. I really shouldn't have this many sequins because they sparkle and then I go on high. Yay for sequins!

Ok I think that's enough of an update. Au revoir mes amies

Yay!!!!! I finally have an LJ but I'm not promising that I will update regularly because I have refuse to turn to the dark side (I won't do it Jen). Well this is very exciting... Also I have mutual friends yay! Before the site kept saying I had no friends and I was getting quite upset but now I have friends. Thanks guys. I still don't know how to work this site because I wanted to add Annie as a friend and I can't remember how to add friends. Also Jen I can't see how I'm supposed to turn my text into rich text. I'm so confused :(

Well I went to a wedding in the weekend. It was my cousins wedding and he was getting married to a russian girl. It's all very scandalous at the moment about the wedding because my cousin met this girlabout a year ago in Kerdistan and since then has been talking to her via email and I think phone as well but he's only seen her in person for about five weeks. Then he paid for her to come to NZ and they decided to get married with only about a months notice to every. It's all very scandalous and my nonie who's a bit racist (just a bit) has been talking about it quite alot.

Jen, I see the rich text button! Ohh so many buttons now.... Ok I'm going to add an image just because it's exciting. Jen, I can't add an image this isn't fair!

Alright that's enough of an update, bye.
